question: Show monthly spend for Addison Johnson.
text: Here is the monthly spend for Addison Johnson for July and August.
sql_used:
SELECT LOWER(service_month) AS service_month, SUM(total_cost) AS total_cost
FROM invoices
WHERE LOWER(student_name) LIKE LOWER('%addison johnson%')
  AND LOWER(service_month) IN ('july', 'august')
GROUP BY LOWER(service_month)
ORDER BY CASE WHEN LOWER(service_month) = 'july' THEN 1 WHEN LOWER(service_month) = 'august' THEN 2 ELSE 3 END
html:
Service MonthTotal Spend ($)
July$6,950.75
August$5,178.60

question: Show monthly hours for Addison Johnson.
text: Here is the monthly hours data for Addison Johnson for the months July through October.
sql_used:
SELECT LOWER(i.service_month) AS service_month, SUM(ili.hours) AS total_hours
FROM invoices i
JOIN invoice_line_items ili ON i.id = ili.invoice_id
WHERE LOWER(ili.student) LIKE LOWER('%addison johnson%')
GROUP BY LOWER(i.service_month)
ORDER BY MIN(strftime('%m', i.invoice_date)) ASC

question: Show vendors with increasing spend over the last three months.
text: No vendors in your district have shown increasing spend over the last three months (August, September, October).
sql_used:
WITH monthly_vendor_spend AS (
  SELECT v.id AS vendor_id, v.name AS vendor_name, LOWER(i.service_month) AS service_month, 
         SUM(i.total_cost) AS total_spend,
         MIN(strftime('%Y-%m', i.invoice_date)) AS year_month
  FROM invoices i
  JOIN vendors v ON v.id = i.vendor_id
  WHERE i.service_month IN ('august', 'september', 'october')
  GROUP BY v.id, v.name, LOWER(i.service_month)
),
ranked_spend AS (
  SELECT vendor_id, vendor_name, service_month, total_spend,
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY vendor_id ORDER BY year_month) AS month_rank
  FROM monthly_vendor_spend
),
spend_trends AS (
  SELECT a.vendor_id, a.vendor_name
  FROM ranked_spend a
  JOIN ranked_spend b ON a.vendor_id = b.vendor_id AND a.month_rank = 1 AND b.month_rank = 2
  JOIN ranked_spend c ON a.vendor_id = c.vendor_id AND a.month_rank = 2 AND c.month_rank = 3
  WHERE a.total_spend < b.total_spend AND b.total_spend < c.total_spend
)
SELECT DISTINCT vendor_id, vendor_name
FROM spend_trends
ORDER BY vendor_name
html: No vendors in your district have shown increasing spend over the last three months (August, September, October).

question: Show clinicians with increasing hours over the last three months.

sql_used:
WITH monthly_hours AS (
  SELECT ili.clinician,
         LOWER(i.service_month) AS service_month,
         SUM(ili.hours) AS total_hours
  FROM invoice_line_items ili
  JOIN invoices i ON ili.invoice_id = i.id
  WHERE LOWER(i.service_month) IN ('august', 'september', 'october')
  GROUP BY ili.clinician, LOWER(i.service_month)
),
ranked_hours AS (

         ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY clinician ORDER BY CASE LOWER(service_month) WHEN 'august' THEN 1 WHEN 'september' THEN 2 WHEN 'october' THEN 3 END) AS rn
  FROM monthly_hours
),
increasing_clinicians AS (
  SELECT a.clinician
  FROM ranked_hours a
  JOIN ranked_hours b ON a.clinician = b.clinician AND a.rn = 1 AND b.rn = 2

question: Show clinicians with decreasing hours over the last three months.
text: Here are the clinicians with decreasing hours over the last three months (August, September, October) in your district.
sql_used:
WITH monthly_hours AS (
  SELECT ili.clinician,
         LOWER(i.service_month) AS service_month,
         SUM(ili.hours) AS total_hours
  FROM invoice_line_items ili
  JOIN invoices i ON ili.invoice_id = i.id
  WHERE LOWER(i.service_month) IN ('august', 'september', 'october')
  GROUP BY ili.clinician, LOWER(i.service_month)
),
ranked_hours AS (
  SELECT clinician,
         service_month,
         total_hours,
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY clinician ORDER BY CASE WHEN service_month = 'august' THEN 1 WHEN service_month = 'september' THEN 2 WHEN service_month = 'october' THEN 3 END) AS rn
  FROM monthly_hours
),
hours_pivot AS (
  SELECT clinician,
         MAX(CASE WHEN service_month = 'august' THEN total_hours ELSE 0 END) AS august_hours,
         MAX(CASE WHEN service_month = 'september' THEN total_hours ELSE 0 END) AS september_hours,
         MAX(CASE WHEN service_month = 'october' THEN total_hours ELSE 0 END) AS october_hours
  FROM ranked_hours
  GROUP BY clinician
)
SELECT clinician, august_hours, september_hours, october_hours
FROM hours_pivot
WHERE august_hours > september_hours AND september_hours > october_hours
ORDER BY august_hours DESC

SELECT SUM(total_cost) AS total_spend
FROM invoices
WHERE LOWER(service_month) = LOWER('September')

question: Show district spend since the start of the 2025 school year.
text: Here is the district spend since the start of the 2025 school year, broken down by month.
sql_used:
SELECT LOWER(service_month) AS service_month, SUM(total_cost) AS total_cost
FROM invoices
WHERE strftime('%Y', invoice_date) = '2025'
GROUP BY LOWER(service_month)
ORDER BY MIN(strftime('%m', invoice_date)) ASC
